BFO:0000002.rdfs:label: continuant
BFO:0000002.IAO:0000115: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

BFO:0000003.rdfs:label: occurrent
BFO:0000003.IAO:0000115: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

BFO:0000004.rdfs:label: independent continuant
BFO:0000004.IAO:0000115: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.

BFO:0000020.rdfs:label: specifically dependent continuant
BFO:0000020.IAO:0000115: A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities. Every instance of A requires some specific instance of B which must always be the same.

BFO:0000031.rdfs:label: generically dependent continuant
BFO:0000031.IAO:0000115: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.

BFO:0000015.rdfs:label: process
BFO:0000015.IAO:0000115: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.

BFO:0000040.rdfs:label: material entity
BFO:0000040.IAO:0000115: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

BFO:0000017.rdfs:label: realizable entity
BFO:0000017.IAO:0000115: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

PATO:0000001.rdfs:label: quality
PATO:0000001.IAO:0000115: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

GO:0008150.rdfs:label: biological_process
GO:0008150.IAO:0000115: A biological process represents a specific objective that the organism is genetically programmed to achieve. Biological processes are often described by their outcome or ending state, e.g., the biological process of cell division results in the creation of two daughter cells (a divided cell) from a single parent cell. A biological process is accomplished by a particular set of molecular functions carried out by specific gene products (or macromolecular complexes), often in a highly regulated manner and in a particular temporal sequence.

PCO:0000005.rdfs:label: population process
PCO:0000005.IAO:0000115: A process that has as primary participant a population. Includes processes such as population growth, extinction, evolution, selection, and adaptation. Population processes may depend on the processes of individual organisms {e.g., population growth reflects the cumulative multicellular organism reproduction (GO:0032504) and death (GO:0016265) of all individuals in a population}, but cannot be described for an individual organism. Some of these processes (e.g., evolution, extinction) can also occur at the species level, so PCO distinguishes between, for example, population extinction and species extinction.

PCO:0000022.rdfs:label: species extinction
PCO:0000022.IAO:0000115: A process that ultimately leads to the death of all individuals in a population.

ENVO:01000744.rdfs:label: human dwelling
ENVO:01000744.IAO:0000115: A self-contained constructed feature used by one or more households as a home, such as a house, apartment, mobile home, houseboat or other 'substantial' structure. A dwelling typically includes nearby outbuildings, sheds etc. within the curtilage of the property, excluding any 'open fields beyond'. It has significance in relation to search and seizure, conveyancing of real property, burglary, trespass, and land use planning.

ENVO:01001369.rdfs:label: tidal mangrove shrubland
ENVO:01001369.IAO:0000115: A shrubland biome which is densely vegetated by dwarf or short mangroves (and associates) that are generally less than 6 meters in height, is tidally influenced,  is located in tropical or subtropical areas.

PCO:0000031.rdfs:label: organismal entity
PCO:0000031.IAO:0000115: A material entity that is one or more organisms, viruses or viroids.

BFO:0000023.rdfs:label: role
BFO:0000023.IAO:0000115: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.

PATO:0001236.rdfs:label: process quality
PATO:0001236.IAO:0000115: A quality which inheres in an process.

PATO:0001241.rdfs:label: physical object quality
PATO:0001241.IAO:0000115: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

IAO:0000027.rdfs:label: data item
IAO:0000027.IAO:0000115: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

GO:0007610.rdfs:label: behavior
GO:0007610.IAO:0000115: The internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of animals (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli, via a mechanism that involves nervous system activity.

GO:0044419.rdfs:label: biological process involved in interspecies interaction between organisms
GO:0044419.IAO:0000115: Any process evolved to enable an interaction with an organism of a different species.

GO:0051703.rdfs:label: biological process involved in intraspecies interaction between organisms
GO:0051703.IAO:0000115: Any process in which an organism has an effect on an organism of the same species.

GO:0051704.rdfs:label: multi-organism process
GO:0051704.IAO:0000115: A biological process which involves another organism of the same or different species.

PCO:0000011.rdfs:label: population growth
PCO:0000011.IAO:0000115: A process that leads to a change in the number of individuals (positive or negative) in a population.

PCO:0000021.rdfs:label: population extinction
PCO:0000021.IAO:0000115: A population process that ultimately leads to the death of all individuals in a population.

PCO:1000001.rdfs:label: population migration
PCO:1000001.IAO:0000115: A population process during which a population moves from one area to another.

PCO:0000000.rdfs:label: collection of organisms
PCO:0000000.IAO:0000115: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.

CARO:0001010.rdfs:label: organism or virus or viroid
CARO:0001010.IAO:0000115: Material anatomical entity that is a member of an individual species or is a viral or viroid particle.

PCO:0000024.rdfs:label: household
PCO:0000024.IAO:0000115: An organismal entity that consists of one or more people who live in the same dwelling and also share at meals or living accommodation, and may consist of a single family or some other grouping of people.

PATO:0000069.rdfs:label: deviation (from_normal)
PATO:0000069.IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

PATO:0000070.rdfs:label: amount
PATO:0000070.IAO:0000115: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

PATO:0000461.rdfs:label: normal
PATO:0000461.IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting no deviation from normal or average.

PATO:0002302.rdfs:label: decreased process quality
PATO:0002302.IAO:0000115: A quality of a process that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0002304.rdfs:label: increased process quality
PATO:0002304.IAO:0000115: A quality of a process that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0001018.rdfs:label: physical quality
PATO:0001018.IAO:0000115: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

PATO:0001555.rdfs:label: has number of
PATO:0001555.IAO:0000115: The number of parts of a particular type that the bearer entity has. This is a relational quality, and thus holds between two entities: the bearer of the quality, and the type of parts.

PATO:0002003.rdfs:label: population quality
PATO:0002003.IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an entire population or part of a population.

PATO:0002303.rdfs:label: decreased object quality
PATO:0002303.IAO:0000115: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0002305.rdfs:label: increased object quality
PATO:0002305.IAO:0000115: A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

PCO:0000048.rdfs:label: invisible to unaided eye
PCO:0000048.IAO:0000115: A physical object quality that is inhered in a material entity that is too small to be viewed by the unaided eye.

IAO:0000102.rdfs:label: data about an ontology part
IAO:0000102.IAO:0000115: Data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

IAO:0000109.rdfs:label: measurement datum
IAO:0000109.IAO:0000115: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

GO:0035176.rdfs:label: social behavior
GO:0035176.IAO:0000115: Behavior directed towards society, or taking place between members of the same species. Occurs predominantly, or only, in individuals that are part of a group.

PCO:0000012.rdfs:label: logistic population growth
PCO:0000012.IAO:0000115: A population process that leads to an increase in the numbers of individuals in a population following a logistic (S-shaped) curve. Generally occurs when the population has a carrying capacity in a particular habitat.

PCO:0000013.rdfs:label: exponential population growth
PCO:0000013.IAO:0000115: A population growth process that leads to an exponential increase in the number of individuals in a population.

PCO:1000002.rdfs:label: human population migration
PCO:1000002.IAO:0000115: A population migration during which a population of humans moves from one area to another with the intention of settling permanently in the new location.

PCO:0000018.rdfs:label: single-species collection of organisms
PCO:0000018.IAO:0000115: A material entity that has as parts two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids of the same species and no members of any other species.

PCO:0000029.rdfs:label: multi-species collection of organisms
PCO:0000029.IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms that consists of two or more organisms from at least two species.

PCO:0000059.rdfs:label: taxon as collection of organisms
PCO:0000059.IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms that has as members every organism of a taxon and no organisms of any other equal or higher ranked taxon. The taxon may be at any level. If the taxon is species, then this is the same as the class species as a collection of organisms. When defining a taxon, it is generally understood that members include both living organisms and dead organisms that are known through specimens or observations.

PCO:0001000.rdfs:label: pair of interacting organisms
PCO:0001000.IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms that consists of exactly two organism, viruses, or viroids that are interacting with each other.

CARO:0010004.rdfs:label: organism
CARO:0010004.IAO:0000115: An individual member of a clade.

ECOCORE:00000045.rdfs:label: symbiotroph
ECOCORE:00000045.IAO:0000115: heterotroph that acquires nutrition from a symbiont

PCO:0000030.rdfs:label: agricultural household
PCO:0000030.IAO:0000115: A household in which the majority of the income of its members is derived from agricultural activities.

PATO:0002300.rdfs:label: increased quality
PATO:0002300.IAO:0000115: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0002301.rdfs:label: decreased quality
PATO:0002301.IAO:0000115: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0000467.rdfs:label: present
PATO:0000467.IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's existence.

PATO:0000161.rdfs:label: rate
PATO:0000161.IAO:0000115: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.

PATO:0000911.rdfs:label: decreased rate
PATO:0000911.IAO:0000115: A rate which is relatively low.

PATO:0000912.rdfs:label: increased rate
PATO:0000912.IAO:0000115: A rate which is relatively high.

PATO:0001019.rdfs:label: mass density
PATO:0001019.IAO:0000115: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence is exerted by the bearer's mass per unit size.

PATO:0001338.rdfs:label: mixed sex
PATO:0001338.IAO:0000115: A biological sex quality inhering in a population of multiple sexes.

PATO:0001415.rdfs:label: morbidity
PATO:0001415.IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a population by virtue of the proportion of its members that are ill at a given time.

PCO:0000003.rdfs:label: quality of a population
PCO:0000003.IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in a population of organisms.

PCO:0000004.rdfs:label: quality of an ecological community
PCO:0000004.IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in a community.

PATO:0001790.rdfs:label: decreased mass density
PATO:0001790.IAO:0000115: A density which is lower relative to the normal or average.

PATO:0001788.rdfs:label: increased mass density
PATO:0001788.IAO:0000115: A density which is higher relative to the normal or average.

IAO:0000078.rdfs:label: curation status specification
IAO:0000078.IAO:0000115: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

IAO:0000225.rdfs:label: obsolescence reason specification
IAO:0000225.IAO:0000115: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

IAO:0000409.rdfs:label: denotator type
IAO:0000409.IAO:0000115: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

STATO:0000047.rdfs:label: count
STATO:0000047.IAO:0000115: a count is a data item denoted by an integer and represented the number of instances or occurences of an entity

PCO:0000033.rdfs:label: human social gathering activity
PCO:0000033.IAO:0000115: A type of social behavior in which a collection of humans intentionally gathers together on a temporary basis to engage socially.

PCO:0000001.rdfs:label: population of organisms
PCO:0000001.IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

PCO:0000017.rdfs:label: species as a collection of organisms
PCO:0000017.IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms that has as members every organism of given species and no organisms of any other species.

PCO:0000020.rdfs:label: family
PCO:0000020.IAO:0000115: A domestic group, or a number of domestic groups linked through descent (demonstrated or stipulated) from a common ancestor, marriage, or adoption.

PCO:0000027.rdfs:label: collection of humans
PCO:0000027.IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms of the same species that has as members only humans.

PCO:0001001.rdfs:label: pair of interacting organisms of the same species
PCO:0001001.IAO:0000115: A pair of interacting  organisms that consists of exactly two organism, viruses, or viroids of the same species that are interacting with each other.

PCO:0000002.rdfs:label: ecological community
PCO:0000002.IAO:0000115: A multi-species collection of organisms of at least two different species, living in a particular area. Must have at least two populations of different species as members.

PCO:0000051.rdfs:label: multi-species collection of microbes
PCO:0000051.IAO:0000115: A multi-species collection of organisms that consists of two or more microbes from at least two species.

CARO:0000012.rdfs:label: multicellular organism
CARO:0000012.IAO:0000115: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of a clade and, at some point in its life-cycle, consists of more than one cell.

PCO:0000073.rdfs:label: alga excluding Cyanobacteria
PCO:0000073.IAO:0000115: An organism that is part of a polyphyletic group of mostly photosynthetic Eukaryotes  encompassing green plants excluding Embriophyta (land plants). Included organisms range from unicellular microalgae, such as Chlorella and diatoms to multicellular forms such as giant kelp.

ECOCORE:00000146.rdfs:label: parasite
ECOCORE:00000146.IAO:0000115: A symbiotroph that reduces the fitness, survival, or growth of its symbiont, often called a host

PCO:0000060.rdfs:label: microbial parasite
PCO:0000060.IAO:0000115: An organism or virus or viroid that is a microbe and a parasite.

PATO:0000470.rdfs:label: increased amount
PATO:0000470.IAO:0000115: An amount which is relatively high.

PATO:0001997.rdfs:label: decreased amount
PATO:0001997.IAO:0000115: An amount which is relatively low.

PCO:0000006.rdfs:label: population birth rate
PCO:0000006.IAO:0000115: The rate of birth of a population of organisms.

PCO:0000007.rdfs:label: population death rate
PCO:0000007.IAO:0000115: The rate of death of a population of organsisms.

PCO:0000008.rdfs:label: population growth rate
PCO:0000008.IAO:0000115: The rate of growth of a population.

PATO:0001164.rdfs:label: dense
PATO:0001164.IAO:0000115: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting density.

PCO:0000057.rdfs:label: overcrowded population
PCO:0000057.IAO:0000115: An increased mass density of a population of organisms such that the density of organisms in an area is increased beyond sustainable levels.

PCO:0000079.rdfs:label: plant density of a population
PCO:0000079.IAO:0000115: The density of plants in a population or organisms (a single species), often measured as the number of plants per area.

PCO:0000081.rdfs:label: seedling density of a population
PCO:0000081.IAO:0000115: The density of seedlings in a population or organisms (a single species), often measured as the number of seedlings per area.

PCO:0000010.rdfs:label: community species richness
PCO:0000010.IAO:0000115: The number of different species represented in an ecological community.

PCO:0000019.rdfs:label: community species diversity
PCO:0000019.IAO:0000115: The number of different species that are represented in a given community, weighted by their abundance. Community species diversity can be calculated in different ways, but consists of two components: species richness and species evenness.

PCO:0000023.rdfs:label: community species evenness
PCO:0000023.IAO:0000115: A quality of an ecological community that reflects how close in abundance all species in a community are.

PCO:0000080.rdfs:label: plant density of an ecological community
PCO:0000080.IAO:0000115: The density of plants in an ecological community (multiple species), often measured as the number of plants per area.

PCO:0000082.rdfs:label: seedling density of an ecological community
PCO:0000082.IAO:0000115: The density of seedlings in an ecological community (multiple species), often measured as the number of plants per area.

IAO:8000001.rdfs:label: base ontology module
IAO:8000001.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that comprises only of asserted axioms local to the ontology, excludes import directives, and excludes axioms or declarations from external ontologies.

IAO:8000002.rdfs:label: editors ontology module
IAO:8000002.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that is intended to be directly edited, typically managed in source control, and typically not intended for direct consumption by end-users.

IAO:8000003.rdfs:label: main release ontology module
IAO:8000003.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that is intended to be the primary release product and the one consumed by the majority of tools.

IAO:8000004.rdfs:label: bridge ontology module
IAO:8000004.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that consists entirely of axioms that connect or bridge two distinct ontology modules. For example, the Uberon-to-ZFA bridge module.

IAO:8000006.rdfs:label: subset ontology module
IAO:8000006.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that is extracted from a main ontology module and includes only a subset of entities or axioms.

IAO:8000013.rdfs:label: reasoned ontology module
IAO:8000013.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that contains axioms generated by a reasoner. The generated axioms are typically direct SubClassOf axioms, but other possibilities are available.

IAO:8000014.rdfs:label: generated ontology module
IAO:8000014.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that is automatically generated, for example via a SPARQL query or via template and a CSV.

PCO:0000054.rdfs:label: number of generations of multicellular organism
PCO:0000054.IAO:0000115: A count data item of the number of steps in the line of descent from a common ancestor for a multicellular organism.

PCO:0000034.rdfs:label: human community event
PCO:0000034.IAO:0000115: A human social event in which humans living in the same area or neighborhood gather to carry out activiites relevent to the people living in the area.

PCO:0000035.rdfs:label: party
PCO:0000035.IAO:0000115: A human social gathering in which the intention is to have a good time. Often the intention is to celebrate something like a birthday, anniversary, or holiday, but there is not always a purpose.

PCO:0000037.rdfs:label: potluck
PCO:0000037.IAO:0000115: A human social gathering at which each participant is expected to bring food to share. A potluck also can be party, a social meal, or some other type of social gathering.

PCO:0000038.rdfs:label: wedding
PCO:0000038.IAO:0000115: A human social gathering at which two people are married. May include a legal or social ceremony.

PCO:0000039.rdfs:label: baby shower
PCO:0000039.IAO:0000115: A human social gathering at which the key participant is an expectant parent and other guests bring presents for the soon to be born baby.

PCO:0000053.rdfs:label: microbial population
PCO:0000053.IAO:0000115: A population of organisms consisting of only microbes of the same species, that live in the same place.

PCO:1000000.rdfs:label: migratory population
PCO:1000000.IAO:0000115: A population which is participating in a migration process.

PCO:0000032.rdfs:label: biological family
PCO:0000032.IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms of the same species whose members are all either genealogically related to each other or have mated with each other.

PCO:1000003.rdfs:label: human migratory population
PCO:1000003.IAO:0000115: A migratory population of humans, travelling with the intention of settling in a new area.

PCO:0000047.rdfs:label: tidal mangrove shrubland community
PCO:0000047.IAO:0000115: An ecological community which is composed primarily of dwarf or short mangroves, often populations of Laguncularia racemosa, Avicennia germinans, Sarcocornia pacifica, or Batis maritima.

PCO:1000004.rdfs:label: microbial community
PCO:1000004.IAO:0000115: An ecological community which is composed of co-existing populations of microbial organisms that interact, directly or indirectly, such that they impact one another's ecological fitness.

PCO:0000078.rdfs:label: seedling density
PCO:0000078.IAO:0000115: The density of seedlings in an ecological community or population, often measured as the number of seedlings per area.

PCO:0000058.rdfs:label: overcrowded human population
PCO:0000058.IAO:0000115: A quality of a human population such that the density humans in an area is increased beyond sustainable levels.

PCO:0000062.rdfs:label: Shannon diversity index
PCO:0000062.IAO:0000115: A community species diversity metric that accounts for both the abundance and evenness of the species present quantified via the following formula: the negative sum of, the product of the proportion of species i relative to the total number of species (pi) multiplied by the natural logarithm of this proportion (ln pi).

PCO:0000063.rdfs:label: Simpson diversity index
PCO:0000063.IAO:0000115: A community species diversity metric that is quantified via the following formula: the reciprocal of the sum of squared proportion of species i relative to the total number of species (pi).

PCO:0000064.rdfs:label: inverse Simpson diversity index
PCO:0000064.IAO:0000115: A community species diversity metric that is quantified via the following formula: the sum of squared proportion of species i relative to the total number of species (pi).

PCO:0000074.rdfs:label: alpha diversity
PCO:0000074.IAO:0000115: A community species diversity that is the mean species diversity at a site or within a specific habitat.

PCO:0000075.rdfs:label: beta diversity
PCO:0000075.IAO:0000115: A community species diversity that is the ratio between regional and local species diversity.

PCO:0000076.rdfs:label: gamma diversity
PCO:0000076.IAO:0000115: A community species diversity that is the total species diversity in a landscape. The area or landscape of interest may be of very different sizes in different situations, but it should encompass multiple sites or habitats as measured by alpha diversity.

IAO:8000005.rdfs:label: import ontology module
IAO:8000005.IAO:0000115: A subset ontology module that is intended to be imported from another ontology.

IAO:8000007.rdfs:label: curation subset ontology module
IAO:8000007.IAO:0000115: A subset ontology that is intended as a whitelist for curators using the ontology. Such a subset will exclude classes that curators should not use for curation.

IAO:8000008.rdfs:label: analysis subset ontology module
IAO:8000008.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that is intended for usage in analysis or discovery applications.

IAO:8000009.rdfs:label: single layer subset ontology module
IAO:8000009.IAO:0000115: A subset ontology that is largely comprised of a single layer or strata in an ontology class hierarchy. The purpose is typically for rolling up for visualization. The classes in the layer need not be disjoint.

IAO:8000010.rdfs:label: exclusion subset ontology module
IAO:8000010.IAO:0000115: A subset of an ontology that is intended to be excluded for some purpose. For example, a blacklist of classes.

IAO:8000012.rdfs:label: species subset ontology module
IAO:8000012.IAO:0000115: A subset ontology that is crafted to either include or exclude a taxonomic grouping of species.

IAO:8000015.rdfs:label: template generated ontology module
IAO:8000015.IAO:0000115: An ontology module that is automatically generated from a template specification and fillers for slots in that template.

PCO:0000061.rdfs:label: parasite isolate population
PCO:0000061.IAO:0000115: A microbial population of parasites that is defined by shared features such as genetic markers reflecting a common origin and distinguishing the population from other related parasite populations.

IAO:8000011.rdfs:label: external import ontology module
IAO:8000011.IAO:0000115: An imported ontology module that is derived from an external ontology. Derivation methods include the OWLAPI SLME approach.

IAO:8000018.rdfs:label: obo basic subset ontology module
IAO:8000018.IAO:0000115:
A subset ontology that is designed for basic applications to continue to make certain simplifying assumptions; many of these simplifying assumptions were based on the initial version of the Gene Ontology, and have become enshrined in many popular and useful tools such as term enrichment tools.

Examples of such assumptions include: traversing the ontology graph ignoring relationship types using a naive algorithm will not lead to cycles (i.e. the ontology is a DAG); every referenced term is declared in the ontology (i.e. there are no dangling clauses).

An ontology is OBO Basic if and only if it has the following characteristics:
DAG
Unidirectional
No Dangling Clauses
Fully Asserted
Fully Labeled
No equivalence axioms
Singly labeled edges
No qualifier lists
No disjointness axioms
No owl-axioms header
No imports

IAO:8000019.rdfs:label: ontology module subsetted by OWL profile
